Inspector Jaime Peña investigates an accident that has left night watchman Ángel Torres in a coma. Security footage reveals Ángel fleeing from his job at the morgue before being struck by a car. Peña is informed that the body of a woman, Mayka Villaverde, has disappeared from the morgue. Mayka, a middle-aged, wealthy businesswoman, was married to a younger man, and apparently suffered a heart attack following a business trip. Her widower, Álex Ulloa, hears the shocking news while with his young mistress, Carla Miller. Álex assures Carla that Mayka is dead.

At the morgue, Álex tells the coroner about Mayka's medical history. Peña is convinced someone stole the body to avoid an autopsy, and is suspicious of Álex, who Peña feels too easily speaks of his wife in the past tense. Peña notes his own wife, Ruth, died 10 years ago in a car accident, and he finds he still speaks of her in the present tense.

Álex hears a loud noise and discovers a busted locker. Inside, he finds a small bottle labeled TH–16, and thinks back earlier in the day, when he puts drops from the same bottle into Mayka's wine. Peña finds him and informs him that Mayka's cell phone is missing. He finds the bottle on Álex, who admits it is a toxin manufactured by Mayka's pharmaceutical company, but he claims he found it on the floor and doesn't know what it does.

More and more events occur at the morgue that seem to be taunting Álex and Carla, convincing Álex that Mayka is still alive and seeking revenge for his affair and murder plot. Álex discovers Mayka hired a private investigator, as she suspected his affair, and had also heard him plotting to kill her. Álex confesses everything to Peña, first telling him he did love Mayka, having met her by chance in Avalon, California. He also met Carla by chance but fell in love with her, and confided in her his darkest secrets. He said that he thinks Mayka only pretended to drink the wine laced with TC–16, which causes a heart attack after eight hours and leaves no trace in the blood, but that she instead took a tranquilizer that made her appear dead.

The police discover incriminating evidence at Álex and Mayka's house, including a map of the morgue. Ángel wakes up from his coma and reveals that after hearing a noise, he saw Mayka's body in the elevator before a figure in a balaclava fired a gun at him, sending him running into the street. Álex insists Mayka is alive and has the means to disappear and that Carla is in danger. Peña informs him they have no evidence Carla Miller exists and that the address he gave for Carla's apartment has been empty for years.

While transporting Álex, the police discover a body in the woods. Álex fears it's Carla, but it's Mayka. Álex tries to escape and Peña runs after him. Álex collapses and claims he needs an ambulance. Peña tells him about the car accident that killed his wife and that she was actually murdered, as her life could have been saved if the other driver had called for help instead of fleeing the scene; Peña and his 10-year-old daughter, Eva, watched helplessly as Ruth died an hour later. He then tells Álex that only recently Eva had remembered the logo on a keychain hanging from the other car's rearview mirror: Avalon, California. It was Álex and Mayka who had fled the scene and left Ruth to die.

Peña then shows Álex a photo of his daughter Eva: Carla Miller. It was Peña and Eva who had taken Mayka's body and conspired to frame him. Eva initially wasn't convinced of their guilt until Álex revealed his darkest secrets to her, including the hit-and-run. Álex, now gasping to breathe, learns that eight hours earlier, Eva had dosed him with TH–16, and his death will be explained as a heart attack brought on by stress

Why people are screaming with bits of information here? Okay, it's a remake of 'El Cuerpo', so what? How many of us have watched El Cuerpo?
El Cuerpo was a critically acclaimed film, which is being remade into many languages like 'Drishyam' directed by Jeethu Joseph. El Cuerpo was already remade into Tamil and Kannada as 'Oru Melliya Kodu' and 'Game' respectively (both are the same film, in fact.). Reportedly it will be remade in English in 2020. It must be that good. I have watched Oru Melliya Kodu and I would still like to watch it in Hindi, because I think Jeethu Joseph can make improvements in the making compared to the Tamil-Kannada version. 
Remaking isn't a bad thing. It becomes a bad thing only when the remake is bad. The Drishyam from Malayalam was remade into Telugu, Kannada, Tamil, Hindi and Sinhalese. The best of those remakes is said to be Paapanasam, thanks to two things: 
1. It was directed by Jeethu Joseph himself.
2. Kamal Haasan was the main lead.
However, none of the remakes was poorly received by the public.
Also note, Sometimes the remaking gets better than the original as well. A recent example is 'Ayogya', the Tamil remake of Telugu film 'Temper'. It got better than the original. A Hindi remake between Temper and Ayogya called 'Simmba' was really bad, though.

হেল্লো, বন্ধুরা আমি অভিরূপ আবার চলে এসেছি এখানে, but এবার একটা exciting খবর নিয়ে, 
Finally, imraan hasmi ফিল্ম আসছে , the bard of blood এর সফলতার পর,তার সাথে প্রায় 1 বছর পর bollywood film এ comeback করল ঋষি কাপুর, তাও আবার "The Body" নামক এই suspense thriller এর হাত ধরে, আমার এই trailer টা দেখে just ধুয়াধার লেগেছে, comeback বোধহয় এটাকেই বলে, আমার এই ভাবনা বা emotion টা তোমাদের সাথে share না করে থাকতে পারলাম না।

Video টা ভালো লাগলে, share করো বাকি film lover দের মধ্যে।

Btw, যারা যারা প্রশ্ন করছ, comeback বলছি কেন, বা ঋষি কাপুর কোথায় ছিল এতদিন, তাহলে বলি
Past 1 বছর মতো, cancer এর মত একটি মরণ রোগ এ যুঝছিলেন, সে কারণেই বিদেশে treatment এর কারণে ফিল্ম থেকে বেশ অনেকটা time ই দুরেছিলেন, কিন্তু এখন সোনা যাচ্ছে ঋষি কাপুর সুস্থ হয়েই আবার bollywood cinema এই মুভি টা দিয়ে comeback করছেন, তাই video টি তে like করে, আমাদের সকলের তরফ থেকে congratulations to veteran ঋষি কাপুর, cancer কে হারানের জন্যে।

এবার আসি ফিল্ম trailer এর বিষয় এ,
Right from the beginning, murder mistery ভরা trailer টা আমার খুব ই intriguing লেগেছে।
একটা suspense triller কিংবা murder mistery ফিল্মের, story খুবই important হয়, যেটা আশা করছি jeethu joseph এর মত mystery thriller specialist justify করবে, অন্তত trailer তঃ সেই ইঙ্গিত এ দিচ্ছে, তোমাদের কি মনে হয়। সাথে এডিটিং এর মান খুবই ভালো, audience কে বেঁধে রাখতে পেরেছে editor.

ঋষি কাপুরের সাথে emran hasmi র film "The Body" আসলে 2012 সালের একটি spanish ফিল্ম এর remake যদিও নাম এ কোনো পরিবর্তন করেনি।
সিনেমা মুক্তি পাবে, 13ই december, 2019.

Scene টার opening হয়, মর্গের একটা dead body cluelessly missing হওয়া দিয়ে। 

Investigating officer হিসেবে ঋষি কাপুর কে যেমন মানানসই লাগছে, ঠিক তেমনি দাপটের সাথে emraan hasmi এর অভিনয়, যেন মনে হচ্ছে আগের web series টার রেস এখনো বর্তমান ওর অভিনরের মধ্যে।

Trailer এ দেখানো storyline এর যে ইঙ্গিত পেয়েছি, তা প্রায় সব মুভি reviewer youtube এ, প্রায় একই angleএ বলে ফেলেছে বা বলবে হয়তো তাই আমার আলাদা করে একই কথা pointless মনে হলো, তাই তোমাদের মাথা না খেয়ে,বাকি বিষয় গুলো আলোচনা করে এখানেই ইতি টানলাম।
তবে storyর তোমাদের নিজের নিজের বেক্ষা, মনোভাব বা কোনো relevant পয়েন্ট যদি মিস করে থাকি, comment box এর লিখে আমাকে ও বাকি viewer দের জানিও।

The film opens with a man running away in fear, looking over his shoulder the whole time. He is hit by a car while on the run and is admitted to the hospital in a coma. The Deputy Commissioner of Police (DCP) Shakthivel is called upon to investigate the matter, where it is found through the security cameras that a corpse of a high profile businesswoman Maaya is missing from the morgue.
Meanwhile, Maaya's husband Akshay is surrounded by his family and friends offering their condolences but he drives them out saying he wants to be left alone. Once they all leave, he drives to his girlfriend Bhumika aka Bhumi's house, where it is revealed Akshay killed his wife and made it look like a heart attack. The police call Akshay over his cell phone and ask him to come to the forensics lab and explain the issue. Akshay drinks a glass of water offered by Bhumi and he leaves. Akshay is asked to stay in the lab until they discover the corpse.
In a series of clues and flashbacks, Akshay is made to believe that Maaya is still alive and is out for revenge. He keeps in contact with Bhumi the entire time, until Shakthivel gets evidence that can allow him to arrest Akshay, in the form of a toxin B-12 that can induce a heart attack. He interrogates Akshay and Akshay reveals how Maaya and him met the first time. After getting locked up in a room, Akshay calls up Bhumi and finds out that Maaya's lawyer Krishna Prasad is in fact a private detective hired by Maaya to spy on Akshay. He asks Bhumi to run away afraid that Maaya is after her. When Bhumi comes out of the building, a car comes speeding towards her and Akshay fears the worst.
He confesses everything to Shakthivel and repeatedly requests him to save Bhumi. Shakthivel gets a call from Deva who says they've found a body, revealed to be Maaya. Shakthivel further confirms that there was no one called Bhumi in the university Akshay mentioned neither in the flat he had gone to and that Bhumi was non-existent. Akshay tries to run away, tailed by Shakthivel.
Shakthivel then reveals that the car accident in which Shakthivel's wife had died was caused by a drunken Akshay and Maaya. Although Shakthivel's daughter Amritha repeatedly calls for help, Maaya tells Akshay to leave them be, due to which wife dies. Amritha had been in a coma for two years and when she woke up, she remembers the car license plate, which she tells her father, who tracks them down. It is revealed in a twist that Bhumi is actually the adult Amritha, Shakthivel's daughter, and this was an elaborate plan orchestrated by Shakthivel and Amritha due to which Maaya was killed. Shakthivel further reveals that the glass of water Amritha had offered Akshay before leaving contained B-12 and it has been eight hours since it entered his bloodstream. Akshay then dies by a heart attack and Shakthivel walks away from his body.

*The film opens with a man running away in fear, looking over his shoulder the whole time. He is hit by a car while on the run and is admitted to the hospital in a coma. The Deputy Commissioner of Police (DCP) Shakthivel is called upon to investigate the matter, where it is found through the security cameras that a corpse of a high profile businesswoman Maaya is missing from the morgue.*

*Meanwhile, Maaya's husband Akshay is surrounded by his family and friends offering their condolences but he drives them out saying he wants to be left alone. Once they all leave, he drives to his girlfriend Bhumika aka Bhumi's house, where it is revealed Akshay killed his wife and made it look like a heart attack. The police call Akshay over his cell phone and ask him to come to the forensics lab and explain the issue. Akshay drinks a glass of water offered by Bhumi and he leaves. Akshay is asked to stay in the lab until they discover the corpse.*

*In a series of clues and flashbacks, Akshay is made to believe that Maaya is still alive and is out for revenge. He keeps in contact with Bhumi the entire time, until Shakthivel gets evidence that can allow him to arrest Akshay, in the form of a toxin B-12 that can induce a heart attack. He interrogates Akshay and Akshay reveals how Maaya and him met the first time. After getting locked up in a room, Akshay calls up Bhumi and finds out that Maaya's lawyer Krishna Prasad is in fact a private detective hired by Maaya to spy on Akshay. He asks Bhumi to run away afraid that Maaya is after her. When Bhumi comes out of the building, a car comes speeding towards her and Akshay fears the worst.*

*He confesses everything to Shakthivel and repeatedly requests him to save Bhumi. Shakthivel gets a call from Deva who says they've found a body, revealed to be Maaya. Shakthivel further confirms that there was no one called Bhumi in the university Akshay mentioned neither in the flat he had gone to and that Bhumi was non-existent. Akshay tries to run away, tailed by Shakthivel.*

*Shakthivel then reveals that the car accident in which Shakthivel's wife had passed away was caused by a drunken Akshay and Maaya. Although Shakthivel's daughter Amritha repeatedly calls for help, Maaya tells Akshay to leave them be, due to which wife dies. Amritha had been in a coma for two years and when she woke up, she remembers the car license plate, which she tells her father, who tracks them down. It is revealed in a twist that Bhumi is actually the adult Amritha, Shakthivel's daughter, and this was an elaborate plan orchestrated by Shakthivel and Amritha due to which Maaya was killed. Shakthivel further reveals that the glass of water Amritha had offered Akshay before leaving contained B-12 and it has been eight hours since it entered his bloodstream. Akshay then dies by a heart attack and Shakthivel walks away from his body.*

🚫🚫🚫SPOILER ALERT🚫🚫🚫
Inspector Rishi Kapoor investigates an accident that has left night watchman in a coma. Security footage reveals watchman fleeing from his job at the morgue before being struck by a car. Rishi is informed that the body of a woman, Sobhita Dhulipala , has disappeared from the morgue. Sobhita, a middle-aged, wealthy businesswoman, was married to a younger man, and apparently suffered a heart attack following a business trip. Her widower, Emraan Hashmi, hears the shocking news while with his young mistress, Vedhika. Emraan assures Vedhika that Sobhita is dead.

At the morgue, Emraan tells the coroner about Sobhita's medical history. Rishi is convinced someone stole the body to avoid an autopsy, and is suspicious of Emraan, who Rishi feels too easily speaks of his wife in the past tense. Rishi notes his own wife, who died 10 years ago in a car accident, and he finds he still speaks of her in the present tense.

Emraan hears a loud noise and discovers a busted locker. Inside, he finds a small bottle labeled TH–16, and thinks back earlier in the day, when he puts drops from the same bottle into Sobhita's wine. Rishi finds him and informs him that Sobhita's cell phone is missing. He finds the bottle on Emraan, who admits it is a toxin manufactured by Sobhita's pharmaceutical company, but he claims he found it on the floor and doesn't know what it does.

More and more events occur at the morgue that seem to be taunting Emraan and Vedhika, convincing Emraan that Sobhita is still alive and seeking revenge for his affair and murder plot. Emraan discovers Sobhita hired a private investigator, as she suspected his affair, and had also heard him plotting to kill her. Emraan confesses everything to Rishi, first telling him he did love Sobhita, having met her by chance in India. He also met Vedhika by chance but fell in love with her, and confided in her his darkest secrets. He said that he thinks Sobhita only pretended to drink the wine laced with TC–16, which causes a heart attack after eight hours and leaves no trace in the blood, but that she instead took a tranquilizer that made her appear dead.

The police discover incriminating evidence at Emraan and Sobhita's house, including a map of the morgue. Watchman wakes up from his coma and reveals that after hearing a noise, he saw Sobhita's body in the elevator before a figure in a balaclava fired a gun at him, sending him running into the street. Emraan insists Sobhita is alive and has the means to disappear and that Vedhika is in danger. Rishi informs him they have no evidence Vedhika exists and that the address he gave for Vedhika's apartment has been empty for years.

While transporting Emraan, the police discover a body in the woods. Emraan fears it's Vedhika, but it's Sobhita. Emraan tries to escape and Rishi runs after him. Emraan collapses and claims he needs an ambulance. Rishi tells him about the car accident that killed his wife and that she was actually murdered, as her life could have been saved if the other driver had called for help instead of fleeing the scene; Rishi and his 10-year-old daughter, Vedhika, watched helplessly as his wife died an hour later. He then tells Emraan that only recently Vedhika had remembered the logo on a keychain hanging from the other car's rearview mirror. It was Emraan and Sobhita who had fled the scene and left Rishi's wife to die.

Rishi then shows Emraan a photo of his daughter Vedhika:who was faking with Emraan as his girlfriend(with other identity) . It was Rishi and Vedhika who had taken Sobhita's body and conspired to frame him. Vedhika initially wasn't convinced of their guilt until Emraan revealed his darkest secrets to her, including the hit-and-run. Emraan, now gasping to breathe, learns that eight hours earlier, Vedhika had dosed him with TH–16, and his death will be explained as a heart attack brought on by stress.
